import sys

def multiply(F, M):
	x =  F[0][0]*M[0][0] + F[0][1]*M[1][0]
	y =  F[0][0]*M[0][1] + F[0][1]*M[1][1]
	z =  F[1][0]*M[0][0] + F[1][1]*M[1][0]
	w =  F[1][0]*M[0][1] + F[1][1]*M[1][1]
	F[0][0] = x
	F[0][1] = y
	F[1][0] = z
	F[1][1] = w

def pwer(F, n):
	if n == 0 or n == 1:
		return
	M = [[1,1],[1,0]]
	pwer(F, n/2)
	multiply(F, F) 
	if n%2 != 0:
		multiply(F, M)

def fib(n):  
	F = [[1,1],[1,0]]
	if n == 0:
		return 0
	pwer(F, n-1)
	return F[0][0]

	while(1):
		s=raw_input()
		a,b = [int(i) for i in s.split(' ')]
		cnt=0
		if a==0 and b==0:
			break
		for i in range(1,500,1):
			if fib(i+1)>=a and fib(i+1)<=b:
				cnt=cnt+1
			else:
				if fib(i+1)>b:
					break
		print(cnt)
	return 0

if __name__=="__main__":
	main()
